= ABOUT =
php-restauth is a client library for the RestAuth protocol [1]. It provides an
interface for all features supported by the protocol. It exclusivly uses JSON as
data format. The library requires the pecl_http extension (see INSTALLATION).

Full API docs are available online at [2] or can be generated using the source
code (see Generating documentation).

[1] https://restauth.net/Specification
[2] https://php.restauth.net

= INSTALLATION =
Please see installation instructions at https://php.restauth.net/.

=== Generating documentation ===
Generating the documentation requires phpDocumentor[1]. If you have it
installed, you can generate documentation simply by running:
	make doc

[1] http://www.phpdoc.org/

= USAGE =
Please see examples/test.php for an extensive example script.

